==Demographics==
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 Census]], S.N.P.J. had a population of 15.<ref name="USCensusEst2020-2021"/> S.N.P.J. once had the distinction of being the least-populated borough in the state (but not municipality; [[East Fork, Pennsylvania|East Fork Road District]], population 14, was less populous) until a mine fire beneath [[Centralia, Pennsylvania|Centralia]] made that borough unsafe to live in.

